bug.short_desc: First login after boot takes over 25 seconds
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1204886 Output of journalctl -b
Description of problem:
The first time I try to log in from gdm after booting it takes over 25 seconds until I get to the desktop. Subsequent logins (after logging out or switching user) do not have this issue. The only suspicious thing I can see in the logs is this:
Sep 26 17:57:10 hp org.gnome.Shell.desktop[1622]: Error creating proxy: Error calling StartServiceByName for org.gtk.vfs.UDisks2VolumeMonitor: Timeout was reached (g-io-error-quark, 24)
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): gnome-shell-3.22.0-1.fc25.x86_64 gnome-session-3.22.0-1.fc25.x86_64 storaged-2.6.2-2.fc25.x86_64
How reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Reboot fedora 25 2. Choose user and log in from gdm
Actual results: It takes about 25 seconds until you get to the desktop
Expected results: The desktop should show up immediately
Additional info: This system is a fresh fedora 24 install from a couple of days ago, which I brought up-to-date before doing a dnf system-upgrade to upgrade it to fedora 25.
Upgrading selinux-policy{,-targeted} from 3.13.1-214.fc25 3.13.1-218.fc25 fixed the issue today.
